                    text="&lt;h4&gt;Five key forces shaping the 2026 automotive industry outlook&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;h4&gt;1.&amp;nbsp;2026&amp;nbsp;light vehicle sales outlook:&amp;nbsp;Flat&amp;nbsp;growth amid mixed regional trends&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Global new vehicle sales rose 3.4% in 2025 to about 91.7 million units, but momentum is easing as global economic growth slows. The S&amp;amp;P Global Economics team&apos;s forecast projects global GDP growth of 2.7% for 2026, down slightly from 2025.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Global light vehicle sales enter 2026 with sales expected to remain steady at around 91.8 million units. This near-flat automotive industry outlook reflects a complex mix of market drivers and risks, including ongoing tariff impacts, semiconductor chip shortages, supply chain uncertainties, high interest rates, and ongoing but uneven EV adoption rates.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rising cost and price pressures, especially in the latter half of 2026, could also limit upside potential.&lt;/p&gt;"/>
