                    text="&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Regional&amp;nbsp;highlights:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Mainland China.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Sales are&amp;nbsp;forecast to decline by&amp;nbsp;about&amp;nbsp;267,000 units in 2026, reflecting&amp;nbsp;pull-ahead&amp;nbsp;demand&amp;nbsp;from 2025 incentives and&amp;nbsp;slower&amp;nbsp;economic growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;North America.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Sales are expected to drop by about 590,000 units&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;19.3&amp;nbsp;million. In the US,&amp;nbsp;accelerated purchases ahead of&amp;nbsp;anticipated&amp;nbsp;price hikes&amp;nbsp;weigh on demand. Mexico&amp;nbsp;faces a challenging year with&amp;nbsp;sales down&amp;nbsp;more than&amp;nbsp;8.7%&amp;mdash;approximately&amp;nbsp;137,000 units.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Western and Central Europe.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;The&amp;nbsp;automotive industry outlook for vehicle sales&amp;nbsp;projects&amp;nbsp;mild growth&amp;nbsp;in 2026, with an increase of 260,000 units to 15.4 million.&amp;nbsp;This increase is&amp;nbsp;driven by improved real incomes, lower&amp;nbsp;inflation&amp;nbsp;and a resilient labor market.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;South Asia.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;India will lead&amp;nbsp;sales growth in 2026, adding 400,000 units. Overall, the region is set to grow by 5.3% to 10.4 million units.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Taken together, these regional shifts underscore the complexity of the 2026 automotive industry outlook, with automakers facing contrasting regional challenges.&lt;/p&gt;"/>
            </section_content1>
            <section_content2
                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/section/v1/section"
